name: pyfesom2
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pyfesom2" %}
{% set version = "0.2.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/FESOM/pyfesom2/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 93ef0df2a714ae617c14f683ee2bcfdac0f40d13b69b6c971928d88f8106a5fb

build:
  number: 2
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - pfplot=pyfesom2.pfplot:pfplot
    - pfinterp=pyfesom2.pfinterp:pfinterp
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv; ls -lR {{ RECIPE_DIR }} {{ SRC_DIR }} {{ SP_DIR }}; cp -rv {{ SRC_DIR }}/pyfesom2/geojson {{ SP_DIR }}/pyfesom2; ls -lR {{ SP_DIR }}/pyfesom2
  always_include_files:
    - pyfesom2/geojson

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - pytest-runner
    - python >=3
  run:
    - cartopy
    - cmocean
    - dask
    - ipython
    - joblib
    - jupyter
    - matplotlib
    - netcdf4
    - numba
    - numpy >=1.17
    - pandas >=0.25
    - pyresample
    - pytest-runner
    - python >=3
    - scipy
    - seawater
    - shapely
    - xarray

test:
  imports:
    - pyfesom2


about:
  home: https://github.com/FESOM/pyfesom2/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: FESOM2 tools
  doc_url: https://pyfesom2.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/FESOM/pyfesom2/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pgierz
    - koldunovn
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.6
